hopobject.body: What's your number? yxhshop.com The key is to ‘break the network at the top’, but that is not so easy. The shadowy figure behind the contraband found in the minivan was traced to an address in Kathmandu but by the time the police raided it the occupant had flown. In the house police found, inter alia, 12 garments partially made out of tiger and leopard skins, more than 100 canine teeth (probably tiger though they have not been analysed), fake passports of different nationalities and identities, large sums of cash in assortedcurrencies and four human skulls – just another set of body parts for onward sale. ‘These guys do everything that makes money,’ Chapagain said.
